# UI/UX Design System

Avoid stark white or neon-green dispensary aesthetics.

## Colors (Tailwind tokens)

| Token | Hex | Use |
|-------|-----|-----|
| `san-mateo-blue` | `#1B365D` | Primary headers/footers |
| `wreath-green` | `#2D5A27` | Secondary accents |
| `sign-red` | `#B23A3A` | High-contrast CTAs |
| `mahogany` | `#2B1D14` | Dark backgrounds / body |
| `stamped-gold` | `#D4AF37` | Borders, highlights |
| `parchment` | `#F5E6C8` | Text, card backgrounds |

## Typography

- **Headers (H1/H2):** Vintage serif — Berkshire Swash for H1; Playfair Display for H2 and other display type.
- **Body:** Clean sans (e.g. Inter), default `text-lg` / 18px, `leading-relaxed` for older readers.

## Product Grids

Style as vintage library catalog cards:

- Use **Synopsis** for descriptions (not generic “Description”).
- Use Dewey Decimal–style catalog numbers instead of standard tags.
